## ğŸ”§ In Shell / Bash

| Context          | Usage                | Meaning                                            |
| ---------------- | -------------------- | -------------------------------------------------- |
| `date -d "@123"` | `@` before a number  | Interpret number as a Unix timestamp               |
| `"$@"`           | All script arguments | Expands to all arguments passed to script/function |
| `'@'` in strings | Character literal    | Just the `@` symbol as a character                 |

---

## ğŸ In Python

| Context         | Usage              | Meaning                                    |
| --------------- | ------------------ | ------------------------------------------ |
| `@decorator`    | Function decorator | Wraps or modifies function behavior        |
| `@classmethod`  | Decorator type     | Defines class-level method                 |
| `@staticmethod` | Decorator type     | Defines method not using class or instance |

---

## ğŸª In Perl

| Context  | Usage    | Meaning                       |
| -------- | -------- | ----------------------------- |
| `@array` | Variable | Declares or accesses an array |

---

## ğŸ’» In C# / .NET

| Context      | Usage    | Meaning                                        |
| ------------ | -------- | ---------------------------------------------- |
| `@variable`  | Verbatim | Allows reserved keyword as identifier          |
| `@"C:\Path"` | Verbatim | Verbatim string literal (ignores escape chars) |

---

## ğŸ“œ In SQL

| Context     | Usage      | Meaning                           |
| ----------- | ---------- | --------------------------------- |
| `@variable` | Variable   | Declares or uses variable (T-SQL) |
| `@@version` | Global var | System-defined variable           |

---

## ğŸ§¾ In JSON/YAML (rare)

| Context        | Usage      | Meaning                             |
| -------------- | ---------- | ----------------------------------- |
| `"@timestamp"` | Field name | Often used for log/event timestamps |

---

## ğŸ“§ In General Text

| Context          | Example            | Meaning                       |
| ---------------- | ------------------ | ----------------------------- |
| Email            | `user@example.com` | Separates username and domain |
| Twitter / Social | `@user`            | Mention or tag a user         |

---

## ğŸ”Œ In Git

| Context              | Usage  | Meaning                                |
| -------------------- | ------ | -------------------------------------- |
| `HEAD@{1}`           | Reflog | Shows prior location of HEAD           |
| `branch@{yesterday}` | Reflog | Time-relative lookup of a branch state |

